Ask HN: How to organize research papers you've read?
text:
I recently started a new role where I have to read a lot of research papers. In past jobs/internships, I've never found a system for organizing the research papers I highlight/annotate. Even worse, I've found it hard to compare notes with my teammates who are often reading the same papers.

Has anybody found a system that they like so far, either on an individual basis or for a team? I find myself defaulting to the standard spreadsheet setup but curious to hear if there's anything more efficient. Thanks!

Show HN: GPT-3 powered Recruiting Email Generator
text:
Hello everyone! Today I am presenting a GPT-3 powered recruiting email generator. Over the past few years, as many of you, I have been receiving an overwhelming number of recruiting emails both directly and via LinkedIn. Last week I was using some of my vacation and browsing through those messages, and I've noticed poorly executed obvious attempts of personalisation some of those have, or being simply poorly worded cold emails.

I thought to myself immediately about potential performance of GPT-3 in that field, and how such email generation could be easily automated, beating most of those human written generic messages.

I have also figured out, once I build such a tech demo, I could then respond to each of those unsummoned recruiting emails with a link to my tool, flipping the coin and turning recruiters into my leads.

Please let me know what you think about it. All feedback is welcome!

Ask HN: Is web design still worth learning in the age of no-code tools and AI?
text:
I've been considering learning web design for some time now, but with the rise of no-code tools, templates, and AI-powered website builders, I'm starting to wonder if it's still worth it.

I understand that having a strong understanding of design principles can give me more flexibility and customization when it comes to building websites. However, it seems like more and more people are using no-code tools and templates to quickly create websites without the need for any specialized knowledge.

So, is learning web design still worth it in 2023?
